			<outline text="August 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="@blacknftart check DM 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 03:11:54 GMT" tweetId="1424931482963906561" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424931482963906561" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="✨ New LA creator industry reporter just dropped ✨ &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/arperelli/status/1424894187988676612&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 02:14:49 GMT" tweetId="1424917119548813318" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424917119548813318" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="@_mecyver check DM 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 01:46:48 GMT" tweetId="1424910066700881924" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424910066700881924" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="@MinnesotaHaze check DM" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 01:44:10 GMT" tweetId="1424909405661798412" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424909405661798412" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="@shawntelco hi I’m a reporter at NYT looking to cover the queenship stuff and would love to chat with you about some of what you’re speaking about on the twitter space rn, if you could DM me after it ends would love to connect! 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 01:36:02 GMT" tweetId="1424907357759311899" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424907357759311899" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="@CallMeLatasha hi I’m a reporter at NYT looking to cover the queenship stuff and would love to chat with you about some of what you’re speaking about on the twitter space rn, if you could DM me after it ends would love to connect! 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 01:34:22 GMT" tweetId="1424906939654283265" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424906939654283265" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Read the story everyone's talking about!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/20lwhuFqST" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 00:20:16 GMT" tweetId="1424888291451576342" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424888291451576342" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;We’re mostly just tickled that The New York Times has finally had to acknowledge the practicality of a term as precise as shitposting in order to engage with a world absolutely filled to the brim with it.&quot;

Me too @TheAVClub, me too 😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.avclub.com/the-new-york-times-learned-a-fun-new-word-for-this-arti-1847450319&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 00:19:21 GMT" tweetId="1424888059712081920" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424888059712081920" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="@TheAVClub Read the full story here!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2021 00:21:15 GMT" tweetId="1424888538068258832" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424888538068258832" inReplyToId="1424888059712081920" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Huge happy b day to @deannaschwartzz!!!!!!!! An absolute star and icon of the industry and only 21 years old &amp;lt;3 🥳 Hope it's the best day!!!" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 23:02:08 GMT" tweetId="1424868630672543746" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424868630672543746" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Conservative twitter learning about Benny Drama today and losing their minds is so entertaining, they do not get it &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/DonaldJTrumpJr/status/1424840331917463556&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 22:38:24 GMT" tweetId="1424862656771485709" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424862656771485709" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Ppl w/ chronic illness and very real disabilities are constantly marginalized or told it’s “all in their head.” It’s disturbing to see this cycle repeat itself w/ those suffering from long Covid. They shouldn’t have to struggle to be taken seriously by media/medical establishment &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/michaelwhitney/status/1424778141848031240&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 20:47:46 GMT" tweetId="1424834814423699456" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424834814423699456" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Ppl w/ chronic illness and very real disabilities are constantly marginalized or told it’s “all in their head.” It’s disturbing to see this cycle repeat itself w/ those suffering from long Covid. They shouldn’t have to struggle to be taken seriously by media/medical establishment &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/michaelwhitney/status/1424778141848031240&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 20:41:21 GMT" tweetId="1424833198861676546" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424833198861676546" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;You conniving little snake rat face. You disgusting little rat. You should not get to talk to another human being as long as you live. You are the bottom of the barrel scum pig of the universe.&quot; Please read every word of @Scaachi's latest &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/scaachikoul/trisha-paytas-youtube-onlyfans-influencer-profile&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 19:06:41 GMT" tweetId="1424809376213200896" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424809376213200896" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;For IG, the shift to shitposting has been a boon as it duels with TikTok for young users. 

While TikTok has seeded many memes into popular culture, more recent ones have gained popularity early among text-heavy IG pages before going mainstream on TikTok&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 19:02:26 GMT" tweetId="1424808306367885312" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424808306367885312" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Inspectors repeatedly found manufacturing and device quality problems with the HeartWare heart pump. But the FDA did not penalize the company, and patients had the device implanted on their hearts without knowing it was faulty and dangerous &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/heartware-patients-implanted-fda&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 18:13:36 GMT" tweetId="1424796015542951936" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424796015542951936" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;The rise of Instagram’s text-heavy meme pages is reminiscent of the early years of Tumblr. Gen Z is rediscovering the old internet and updating it.&quot; Thank you to @continuants for sharing her wisdom in this piece.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:48:00 GMT" tweetId="1424774473698271233" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424774473698271233" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I'm the elderly woman &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Tomas_Mier/status/1424770954178142218&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:37:04 GMT" tweetId="1424771724562767872" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424771724562767872" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;I did it for money, and I got my money, and that’s it. But over time, I think people have seen like, oh, she actually has changed.” This whole piece by @Scaachi is a must read &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/scaachikoul/trisha-paytas-youtube-onlyfans-influencer-profile&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:05:24 GMT" tweetId="1424763755385135104" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424763755385135104" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Everything @Scaachi writes is a masterclass in feature writing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/scaachikoul/trisha-paytas-youtube-onlyfans-influencer-profile&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:01:34 GMT" tweetId="1424762791454334980" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424762791454334980" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;I'm the niche internet micro celeb of the ironic posting community,&quot; Mr. Robbin, 20, said. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 15:56:37 GMT" tweetId="1424761545901240320" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424761545901240320" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I know!! There were so many good ones left on the cutting room floor since we can't embed anything with a swear word 😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/wareisian/status/1424751829699682307&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 15:22:10 GMT" tweetId="1424752873934516225" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424752873934516225" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I did it 😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/NYT_first_said/status/1424748410905759753&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 15:09:00 GMT" tweetId="1424749559993954308" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424749559993954308" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I wrote about the rise of IG's Create Most and Whisper app posts, how self expression has evolved on IG, and why shitposting pages are booming right now &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 15:13:41 GMT" tweetId="1424750740350795784" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424750740350795784" inReplyToId="1424749559993954308" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="For a long time, Twitter was the unofficial CMS for Instagram. Large meme pages grew by reposting tweets. 

Now, reposts of tweets have fallen out of favor and IG Create mode and Whisper app posts have taken their place. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:17:11 GMT" tweetId="1424766719973761024" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424766719973761024" inReplyToId="1424750740350795784" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="“If you see someone following a meme page where they typically post tweets, they have a different sense of humor to what Gen Z would consider to be cool,” said Faris Ibrahim, 18. 
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:17:47 GMT" tweetId="1424766870868008963" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424766870868008963" inReplyToId="1424766719973761024" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="&quot;It's cringe to post tweets, so yeah, we don't do that&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/09/technology/instagram-text-memes.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 16:18:26 GMT" tweetId="1424767036014546946" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424767036014546946" inReplyToId="1424766870868008963" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 8" type="calendarDay" name="08" >
				<outline text="Mortality rates are not everything. People across the country are suffering with potentially lifelong disability and chronic illness due to #longcovid, including many children &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/08/health/long-covid-kids.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 09 Aug 2021 02:18:53 GMT" tweetId="1424555754288140289" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424555754288140289" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Thread &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/feministabulous/status/1424477835767558147&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 23:26:35 GMT" tweetId="1424512394290634752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424512394290634752" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="A girl I interned with at Harper’s Bazaar married a mega rich guy in the Hamptons, doesn’t work anymore and now spends her time reposting insane anti vaxx Qanon conspiracies on IG" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 13:26:32 GMT" tweetId="1424361387069820935" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424361387069820935" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Twitter needs ways to close threads or turn off replies post tweet or mark question tweets as answered" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 12:47:26 GMT" tweetId="1424351545924079621" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424351545924079621" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Has anyone else’s arm never stopped hurting after they got the vaccine? My arm never stopped hurting after I got vaxxed this spring and I’m starting to think it might never go away 😰. Everyone should get vaxxed, very grateful to have gotten Pfizer but genuinely looking for info" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 12:01:57 GMT" tweetId="1424340100842856466" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424340100842856466" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="It’s a very mild soreness and I would take it over getting severe Covid every day. It’s not even a question whether it’s worth the trade off. Everyone should get vaccinated. Just wondering if anyone has any info on this b/c I can’t find anything online. 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 12:05:17 GMT" tweetId="1424340939187777541" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424340939187777541" inReplyToId="1424340100842856466" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					<outline text="Ty to everyone who replied! It seems like this can happen very rarely with a shot if they inject it in the wrong way/place. My arm was hanging out a car window so makes sense it hit a weird nerve or something. Appreciate all who responded and grateful to be fully vaccinated 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Sun, 08 Aug 2021 12:28:17 GMT" tweetId="1424346726517809154" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424346726517809154" inReplyToId="1424340100842856466" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="I can’t wait to watch!!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kll5/status/1424136375817752579&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 22:33:35 GMT" tweetId="1424136669872021504" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424136669872021504" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is an entertaining read but the main thing I love about the internet is people like Cindy (no offense to her at all) aren't the arbiters of anything anymore &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/07/style/cindy-adams-ny-post-only-in-new-york-kids-showtime-documentary-gossip.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 22:12:40 GMT" tweetId="1424131405055811587" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424131405055811587" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The gossip world is very toxic now, but grateful we’ve moved beyond the tabloid heyday and the worldview it pushed. Will definitely watch the doc mentioned in this story too! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/07/style/cindy-adams-ny-post-only-in-new-york-kids-showtime-documentary-gossip.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 22:23:11 GMT" tweetId="1424134049417678848" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424134049417678848" inReplyToId="1424131405055811587" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I do wonder what Cindy would think of Deuxmoi or TikTok Room (rip) though 🙈 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/07/style/cindy-adams-ny-post-only-in-new-york-kids-showtime-documentary-gossip.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 22:30:13 GMT" tweetId="1424135820617785345" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424135820617785345" inReplyToId="1424134049417678848" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&quot;Regardless of who's writing whom, if you're writing a character of a different gender than yours, it's probably just best practice to try interacting with someone of that gender in real life first&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://mashable.com/article/written-by-a-woman-men-writing-women-meme&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 22:03:59 GMT" tweetId="1424129221031383042" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424129221031383042" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Proponents of Ivermectin are “raiding rural farm stores so they can suck down ‘sheep drench’ and take swine injections.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hkanji/status/1424115946709467138&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 21:15:22 GMT" tweetId="1424116983017000962" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424116983017000962" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="“There is a noticeable increase in calls to poison centers regarding Ivermectin being misused. It’s clear that a vast majority are associated with a belief that it will prevent or treat COVID.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thedailybeast.com/demon-sperm-doctors-new-bogus-cure-has-covid-truthers-eating-horse-paste&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 21:17:50 GMT" tweetId="1424117605485342722" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424117605485342722" inReplyToId="1424116983017000962" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="The same old body hacking wellness stunts like freezing cold showers are always being repackaged to treat new things &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1424109744634023937/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 20:46:36 GMT" tweetId="1424109744634023937" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424109744634023937" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Squishmallows have signed with CAA &lt;a href=&quot;https://variety.com/2021/film/news/squishmallows-film-tv-caa-1235035527/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 20:39:53 GMT" tweetId="1424108052869906432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424108052869906432" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I wrote about how Squishmallows were becoming an online phenomenon in March and why the plushies were going so viral &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/16/style/squishmallows.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 20:40:59 GMT" tweetId="1424108332223123456" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424108332223123456" inReplyToId="1424108052869906432" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Media companies: if u want to support people dealing with harassment and abuse then give them time off. Full stop. If a worker is forced to spend hours and hours of overtime dealing w/ harassment that comes *because* of their job that is labor and deserves compensation/time off" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 20:20:54 GMT" tweetId="1424103276975321093" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424103276975321093" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="There’s so much more to be done to help media companies at every level understand these issues, that’s why I’m grateful to be part of a union that advocates for change in the industry 💪🏻" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 20:25:33 GMT" tweetId="1424104446556966914" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1424104446556966914" inReplyToId="1424103276975321093" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="Tucker is now weighing in on Chris Chan &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nezumi_ningen/status/1423818231962275840&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 01:50:58 GMT" tweetId="1423823952380514309" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423823952380514309" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Follow @IAmAsarch who has been doing absolutely phenomenal reporting on the Chris Chan case &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/iamasarch/status/1423820888026324995&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 01:53:33 GMT" tweetId="1423824602661199874" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423824602661199874" inReplyToId="1423823952380514309" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text=".@IAmAsarch also wrote a great rundown of who she is and why she’s such a well known internet figure &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.insider.com/chris-chan-arrested-trending-who-is-mom-twitter-history-sonichu-2021-8&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 07 Aug 2021 01:56:29 GMT" tweetId="1423825341626294274" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423825341626294274" inReplyToId="1423824602661199874" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The only way to work 😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/juiceboxca/status/1423604873585733632&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 21:17:29 GMT" tweetId="1423755130474688512" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423755130474688512" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Work for the rest of the day is cancelled in order to hold the poetry discussion group" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 20:18:40 GMT" tweetId="1423740327458791426" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423740327458791426" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;The very role and meaning of libraries relies on their right to own books, books that can expire are books that can disappear permanently... There is a cultural, a political, even a civilizational danger in this vulnerability that can’t be overestimated&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thenation.com/article/culture/libraries-digital-publishing-ebooks/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 20:15:43 GMT" tweetId="1423739584865705984" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423739584865705984" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="You can now put virtual NFT strippers to work earning you crypto on a platform called Stripperville, which calls itself the “Worlds first digital strip club” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.stripperville.io/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/XzvCSEAjZ1" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 17:07:20 GMT" tweetId="1423692176941219843" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423692176941219843" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@StripperVilleio is an NFT project consisting of 3,000 hand drawn first generation NFTs that are Strippers on the Ethereum blockchain. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.stripperville.io/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/nmVYt0GfIT" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 17:08:47 GMT" tweetId="1423692540922929155" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423692540922929155" inReplyToId="1423692176941219843" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="On Stripperville, “strippers will ONLY be depicted as sexy girls in bikinis.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.stripperville.io/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/kCFUl27PXQ" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 17:10:03 GMT" tweetId="1423692858687594496" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423692858687594496" inReplyToId="1423692540922929155" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="I love how we're just speedrunning dystopia" type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 22:51:11 GMT" tweetId="1423778708381331457" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423778708381331457" inReplyToId="1423692858687594496" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="Just a reminder than @juliacarriew is one of the most talented, dogged and brilliant journalists on this site." type="tweet" created="Fri, 06 Aug 2021 03:20:01 GMT" tweetId="1423483976174370816" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423483976174370816" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="My culture &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/GregBensinger/status/1423419584288153604&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 23:10:04 GMT" tweetId="1423421072041398272" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423421072041398272" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Chandler interrupted the proceedings, loudly saying 'I’m famous on the internet,' before Heilberg told her not to speak until spoken to by the court.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://dailyprogress.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/greene-woman-charged-with-incest-is-denied-bond/article_672612c0-f625-11eb-ae4a-57451e11d882.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 22:23:58 GMT" tweetId="1423409471297003523" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423409471297003523" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="The media desperately needs to better interrogate what type of influencers they platform in glowing profiles and what types of messages those influencers will inevitably promote, using that fame and mainstream clout &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ejdickson/status/1423332535195652101&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 22:10:24 GMT" tweetId="1423406059859763200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423406059859763200" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="It's interesting to read lines like this from politicians about how they view online communities. I feel like it reveals a lot more about the internet bubble they operate in rather than the actual online landscape &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/04/us/politics/biden-democrats.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/QLKteg9nUp" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 19:52:06 GMT" tweetId="1423371255281901569" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423371255281901569" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I reached out to Amazon and TikTok about this. This was an error on TikTok’s end. 

They “temporarily swapped the Amazon ad creative with a different video. The issue has now been fixed.&quot; - TikTok spokesperson &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eddyburback/status/1422972566629543941&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 17:26:22 GMT" tweetId="1423334577657974788" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423334577657974788" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Exactly 💓 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/gawker/status/1423011547895537664&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 16:16:57 GMT" tweetId="1423317108297912328" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423317108297912328" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="“To live in New York is to face a constant stream of indignities… but to be a real New Yorker is to develop a twisted admiration for these things.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gawker.com/culture/new-york-we-like-that-it-sucks&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 16:17:40 GMT" tweetId="1423317288950718474" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423317288950718474" inReplyToId="1423317108297912328" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Trolls have been targeting @WajSKhan &amp;amp; I over the past day. I met Waj at @columbiajourn in 2019 he’s a phenomenal journalist. The allegations these accts are making about him are not true. I’m saddened that journalists these days have to face these attacks for telling the truth." type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 15:16:53 GMT" tweetId="1423301994106654730" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423301994106654730" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="These campaigns are organized to spread disinformation and smear journalists in an effort to discredit their reporting, especially when they cover national security like @WajSKhan does. I’m grateful to consider him a colleague and it’s sad ppl would try to manipulate that." type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 15:21:18 GMT" tweetId="1423303104972292103" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423303104972292103" inReplyToId="1423301994106654730" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Silicon Valley men who say “learn to code” I’d like to see you build one decent tumblr theme" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 08:07:56 GMT" tweetId="1423194042616086536" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423194042616086536" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="This is really, really kind and thank you to whoever did this. @GirlsWhoCode is an amazing organization. 

I was lucky enough to ~learn to code~ in women-taught classes with other women (thanks @girldevelopit!!) and it made all the difference. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1423230192328134658/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 10:31:34 GMT" tweetId="1423230192328134658" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423230192328134658" inReplyToId="1423194042616086536" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Also to anyone thinking of taking a class, even though I never use the technical skills I developed learning HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Ruby on Rails, PHP (ugh) and teaching myself C# for Unity that one year I got really into VR lol. It all helped me discover my love for technology💓" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 10:39:22 GMT" tweetId="1423232152200564738" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423232152200564738" inReplyToId="1423230192328134658" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I feel like I already know people like this &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bimbopolitic/status/1423071648840921093&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 06:03:25 GMT" tweetId="1423162709768425474" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423162709768425474" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="People are taking the 00s nostalgia too far worshiping rich people again and trying to act like downtown Manhattan is cool" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 04:27:22 GMT" tweetId="1423138538183270400" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423138538183270400" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="August 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="Me learning that people regularly use and check &quot;email&quot; instead of DMing and text like normal ppl &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1423076296171556866/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 00:20:03 GMT" tweetId="1423076296171556866" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423076296171556866" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Life would be a whole lot better if everyone would kindly embrace my method &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2019/01/case-inbox-infinity/579673/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/eqEEjGcnJL" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 00:26:43 GMT" tweetId="1423077974018977796" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423077974018977796" inReplyToId="1423076296171556866" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="This was extremely inevitable &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nypost/status/1422227107946635265&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 23:19:36 GMT" tweetId="1423061083170820096" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423061083170820096" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I ASPIRE &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nyttypos/status/1423058512050106368&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 23:16:33 GMT" tweetId="1423060318385696770" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423060318385696770" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="American Airlines passengers can now get 30 min of free access to TikTok while in the air &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnet.com/tech/services-and-software/tiktok-your-new-in-flight-entertainment-option/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 23:10:50 GMT" tweetId="1423058877445066752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423058877445066752" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Gonna carry this and fill it with red sauce &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hypebae/status/1422947535656718341&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 21:23:31 GMT" tweetId="1423031870380380160" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423031870380380160" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Insider got inside David Dobrik's big Lallapalooza &quot;house party&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.insider.com/david-dobriks-lollapalooza-chicago-party-photos-price-2021-8&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/fWdZkbed2b" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 20:16:40 GMT" tweetId="1423015048729939969" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423015048729939969" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Amazon said these are not official Amazon ads and they are investigating the matter with TikTok &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eddyburback/status/1422972566629543941&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 19:59:05 GMT" tweetId="1423010622480949249" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423010622480949249" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="It looks like an Amazon marketplace seller potentially bought the ads, will update if I get any more info from Amazon or TikTok &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eddyburback/status/1422973622801506306&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 19:59:56 GMT" tweetId="1423010836784631808" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423010836784631808" inReplyToId="1423010622480949249" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="There we go! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/teamsweeting/status/1422979683931541509&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 21:22:16 GMT" tweetId="1423031555753091073" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423031555753091073" inReplyToId="1423010836784631808" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="GOT THE ANSWER TO THIS MYSTERY. It was a hilarious mistake by a TikTok glitch. “This situation was the result of a technical issue, which temporarily swapped the Amazon ad creative with a different video. The issue has now been fixed.&quot; - TikTok spokesperson. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eddyburback/status/1422972566629543941&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 03:15:37 GMT" tweetId="1423120478747512835" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423120478747512835" inReplyToId="1423010622480949249" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="It’s sad because this ad is better than anything I’ve ever seen a brand produce for the internet &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eddyburback/status/1422972566629543941/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 03:34:27 GMT" tweetId="1423125218197868549" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423125218197868549" inReplyToId="1423120478747512835" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="@RGA make this person a creative director u cowards &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hshaban/status/1423017760985079810&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 03:37:33 GMT" tweetId="1423126000372654080" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423126000372654080" inReplyToId="1423125218197868549" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/personal-finance/used-renters-insurance-to-pay-off-student-loans-2021-8&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/bY86gxABZO" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 19:24:56 GMT" tweetId="1423002030503698432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423002030503698432" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is one of those &quot;make it stop&quot; TikToks &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/tomgara/status/1422998075476529155&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 19:20:36 GMT" tweetId="1423000937249927173" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423000937249927173" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Love going on TV/radio, but if you're a YouTuber covering one of my stories or something I've written abt and you want to have me on to chat about it please reach out!! :D I'd love to do more interviews with YTers, streamers, etc! Reach out on taylor.lorenz at nytimes dot com" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 17:41:33 GMT" tweetId="1422976010673291270" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422976010673291270" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@ColinandSamir can attest, I'm not a horrible guest!!" type="tweet" created="Wed, 04 Aug 2021 17:42:08 GMT" tweetId="1422976159084548097" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422976159084548097" inReplyToId="1422976010673291270" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="@ColinandSamir Things I'm happy to chat about w/ YouTubers:
- internet culture stuff
- &quot;creator economy&quot;
- tech news
- meme culture 
- social media (TikTok, Twitter, IG, etc)
