				<outline text="YouTube Shorts $100M creator fund launches today. 

Creators who’ve posted the most engaging Shorts content in the month of July will begin receiving payments of up to $10k early next week
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/08/03/business/economy-stock-market-news/youtube-begins-paying-out-100-million-to-creators-using-its-short-form-video-feature&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 16:15:00 GMT" tweetId="1422591842638393348" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422591842638393348" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The Shorts creator fund is invitation-only with no application process. Each month, YouTube will reach out to several thousand creators whose Shorts are generating high engagement and inform them of their earnings retroactively. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/08/03/business/economy-stock-market-news/youtube-begins-paying-out-100-million-to-creators-using-its-short-form-video-feature&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 16:16:07 GMT" tweetId="1422592124176928769" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422592124176928769" inReplyToId="1422591842638393348" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Creators need to set up an account with AdSense to collect earnings, which could range from $100 to $10,000 a month. 

Creators can be eligible for multiple months in a row, but not all will be. It’s all about if you make it into that top 1%. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/08/03/business/economy-stock-market-news/youtube-begins-paying-out-100-million-to-creators-using-its-short-form-video-feature&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 16:17:49 GMT" tweetId="1422592552092389379" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422592552092389379" inReplyToId="1422592124176928769" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="More in my story 👇🏻 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/08/03/business/economy-stock-market-news/youtube-begins-paying-out-100-million-to-creators-using-its-short-form-video-feature&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 03 Aug 2021 16:18:14 GMT" tweetId="1422592655494586375" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422592655494586375" inReplyToId="1422592552092389379" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
