				<outline text="I wrote about a new startup called F*** You Pay Me, that's building basically a Glassdoor for influencers, and the power shift from traditional brands to the creators &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/02/technology/fypm-creators-app-pay.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 15:35:45 GMT" tweetId="1422219579330228230" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422219579330228230" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="There has been a HUGE move toward more pay transparency in the creator world, F*** You Pay Me is part of that.

Founded by a content creator and former Facebook data scientist, they came out of a tech startup incubator program, launched in beta last month &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/02/technology/fypm-creators-app-pay.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 15:37:49 GMT" tweetId="1422220096567529480" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422220096567529480" inReplyToId="1422219579330228230" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="What originally caught my attn was the founder's announcement of her company which was a strong rebuke of inequalities in the &quot;creator economy&quot;. It's a MUST READ for anyone who cares about this industry. 

Every &quot;creator economy&quot; investor should read this! &lt;a href=&quot;https://msyoungprofessional.com/?p=622&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PwmtFILou8" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 15:43:48 GMT" tweetId="1422221602259836933" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422221602259836933" inReplyToId="1422220096567529480" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
