				</outline>
			<outline text="August 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="Extra extra read all about it! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/z7sv1Ra9I6" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 01:19:28 GMT" tweetId="1422004087868952577" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422004087868952577" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Tinx is always on brand! It's what makes her an effective influencer :) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JordanUhl/status/1421996383981215745&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 01:08:07 GMT" tweetId="1422001230507741185" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1422001230507741185" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="In May, the Knight Foundation announced a $125k investment in a an online influencer campaign to identify local influencers in San Jose w/ up to 100k followers, and connect them with city officials to broadcast public health information about the vaccines &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:52:52 GMT" tweetId="1421997391876530176" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421997391876530176" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I think so!! 🥰 Hope people read my story and find it informative &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/XuAdafcip9" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 22:38:41 GMT" tweetId="1421963622507454464" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421963622507454464" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I spoke to @Rob_Flaherty about the White House leveraging content creators to boost vaccination rates &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/by94Ujzl97" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 21:41:08 GMT" tweetId="1421949140552937476" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421949140552937476" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about how the White House, as well as state and local governments, are leveraging influencers to fight back against vaccine misinformation and encourage people to get vaccinated &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 21:01:44 GMT" tweetId="1421939224199106560" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421939224199106560" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="According data analysis, “when large numbers of influencers post in the same time period, vaccination rates go up,” said Rob Perry, founder and CEO of @XOMAD, which has worked with state and local governments across the country to lead these campaigns &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 21:35:56 GMT" tweetId="1421947832425095173" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421947832425095173" inReplyToId="1421939224199106560" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="New Jersey, Oklahoma City County, Guildford County, N.C., as well as cities like San Jose, Calif, and several counties in Colorado (and soon Texas) are running influencer marketing campaigns aimed at boosting vaccination rates &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 21:37:52 GMT" tweetId="1421948320017092608" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421948320017092608" inReplyToId="1421947832425095173" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Colorado awarded a contract worth up to $16.4 million to the Denver-based Idea Marketing, which includes a program to pay creators in the state $400 to $1,000 a month to promote the vaccines. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:27:52 GMT" tweetId="1421991100911210497" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421991100911210497" inReplyToId="1421948320017092608" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="CO's health department said that influencers were being paid in exchange for posting because “all too often, diverse communities are asked to reach out to their communities for free. And to be equitable, we know we must compensate people for their work.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:31:11 GMT" tweetId="1421991937486192642" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421991937486192642" inReplyToId="1421991100911210497" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="Officials &amp;amp; influencers hope their pro-vaccination messaging will serve to counter the often very loud vaccine skeptics online. &quot;If we view disinformation as a negative information effort, this campaign is a positive information effort,&quot; @Rob_Flaherty said &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:41:25 GMT" tweetId="1421994511924797440" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421994511924797440" inReplyToId="1421991937486192642" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
										<outline text="As these local influencer campaigns continue to roll out in states and cities across the country, please let me know if you see any in your area!! 

You can email links or screenshots to me at: taylor dot lorenz @ nytimes dot com &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:50:26 GMT" tweetId="1421996778681896965" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421996778681896965" inReplyToId="1421994511924797440" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
											<outline text="Didn't make it in the final story, but @AidanKohnMurphy and Gen Z for Change, a collective of hundreds of popular creators, have banded together to promote vaccination to young people and are helping to seed an organic movement to combat vaccine misinfo! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/gen_zforchange/status/1419754023608061953&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 00:56:50 GMT" tweetId="1421998392931016708" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421998392931016708" inReplyToId="1421996778681896965" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
												<outline text="&quot;You're constantly being fed misinfo about the vaccine,&quot; said TikToker Victoria Hammett. &quot;You have The Republican Hype House &amp;amp; others pushing out anti-vaxx messaging. They have a network similar to us where their creators are always posting misinformation&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/08/01/technology/vaccine-lies-influencer-army.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 02 Aug 2021 01:01:55 GMT" tweetId="1421999668507021315" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421999668507021315" inReplyToId="1421998392931016708" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
													<outline text="Interesting follow up-- Influencer says she lost 4,000 IG followers and sponsors dropped her after she promoted the vaccine 👇🏻 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ThatGirlShaeXo/status/1423048568563175424&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; h/t @grlsct" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 00:27:44 GMT" tweetId="1423078230936809475" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423078230936809475" inReplyToId="1421999668507021315" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
													<outline text="Interesting follow up-- Influencer says she lost 4,000 IG followers and people tried to get sponsor to drop her after she promoted the vaccine 👇🏻 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ThatGirlShaeXo/status/1423048568563175424&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 05 Aug 2021 00:41:08 GMT" tweetId="1423081603874529283" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1423081603874529283" inReplyToId="1421999668507021315" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
													</outline>
												</outline>
											</outline>
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Can someone who knows more about this than I do explain why Heather Young from Selling Sunset and Tarek and his kids are always traveling around in one of these giant vans??? Like why aren’t they driving around in a normal car? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1421925675846365184/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 01 Aug 2021 20:07:53 GMT" tweetId="1421925675846365184" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421925675846365184" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 31" type="calendarDay" name="31" >
				<outline text="Missing nyc already 😭 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1421525364778565633/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 17:37:12 GMT" tweetId="1421525364778565633" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421525364778565633" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="😒 &lt;a href=&quot;https://deadline.com/2021/07/los-angeles-covid-surge-driven-by-white-affluent-neighborhoods-1234802675/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 01:49:17 GMT" tweetId="1421286815701430276" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421286815701430276" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Damn &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1421270940034367490/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 00:46:12 GMT" tweetId="1421270940034367490" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421270940034367490" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Humbled to receive all the clout of a New Yorker byline without any of the work 😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/chaykak/status/1421246335102095368&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 00:01:25 GMT" tweetId="1421259668500873216" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421259668500873216" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Bored Ape Yacht Club is a combo gated online community, stock-shareholding group, art collection, streetwear brand, hedge fund, and a user-generated universe of intellectual property.

Ty @chaykak for this explainer on ape avatars cropping up everywhere! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newyorker.com/culture/infinite-scroll/why-bored-ape-avatars-are-taking-over-twitter&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 19:37:56 GMT" tweetId="1421193361210286088" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421193361210286088" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I really used to have faith in humanity before the internet 😌" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 18:06:55 GMT" tweetId="1421170455096872960" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421170455096872960" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Schwartzie14/status/1421111294984433666&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 16:55:53 GMT" tweetId="1421152581603057664" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421152581603057664" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Kahlil Greene was elected as the first Black student body president at Yale and has nearly a half-million followers on TikTok. After taking a semester off to focus on TikTok, Mr. Greene plans to graduate from Yale this Dec. 
A must read by @MissAdenikeO! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/30/style/kahlil-greene-yale-president-black-genz-historian.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 16:06:30 GMT" tweetId="1421140150688522242" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421140150688522242" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="My people! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/38-percent-remote-workers-work-bed-f8708125-a068-47ff-9519-bb7870011cd5.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 15:31:39 GMT" tweetId="1421131381879410692" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421131381879410692" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I wrote about this topic last year &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/31/style/working-from-bed.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 15:32:43 GMT" tweetId="1421131650977583105" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421131650977583105" inReplyToId="1421131381879410692" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I could “protect my well-being” a lot better if employers actually gave time off for mental health &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nytimes/status/1420806374699806721&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 14:45:06 GMT" tweetId="1421119668761202692" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421119668761202692" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Love having to perform at peak level in the midst of a global pandemic with people I love dying around me while I try to process unimaginable grief while being repeatedly doxxed and pummeled with online harassment, and getting no comp time to deal with it" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 14:55:48 GMT" tweetId="1421122360292241409" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421122360292241409" inReplyToId="1421119668761202692" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1421124116694790151/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 15:02:47 GMT" tweetId="1421124116694790151" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1421124116694790151" inReplyToId="1421119668761202692" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="“The actual disease typically lasts about 2 weeks, but after the virus is gone, people aren't recovered. 

Covid-19 sets off biological processes that can produce long-term effects even in people who had mild or no symptoms at the start.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/long-covid-can-cause-memory-problems-does-it-raise-alzheimer-n1275396&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 03:12:32 GMT" tweetId="1420945376887009282" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420945376887009282" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="“The majority of people with Covid-19 do not end up in the ICU, but a lot of people still have cognitive impairment that greatly impacts their lives. 

It creates a disability in patients who never got very sick.&quot; 
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/long-covid-can-cause-memory-problems-does-it-raise-alzheimer-n1275396&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 03:16:51 GMT" tweetId="1420946461609512966" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420946461609512966" inReplyToId="1420945376887009282" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Breakthrough cases can still lead to long covid. Even if u have a mild/asymptomatic case you can end up disabled, chronically ill w/ long covid. Hope everyone who is vaxxed keeps safe and avoids this potentially debilitating virus. Obv get vaxxed if ur not &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/long-covid-can-cause-memory-problems-does-it-raise-alzheimer-n1275396&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 03:30:16 GMT" tweetId="1420949841023148038" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420949841023148038" inReplyToId="1420946461609512966" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="“The more severe the loss of smell, the more severe the loss of memory will be.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/long-covid-can-cause-memory-problems-does-it-raise-alzheimer-n1275396&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 30 Jul 2021 03:10:39 GMT" tweetId="1420944904155398144" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420944904155398144" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Nothing beats the value of a high quality education, that's why I went to &lt;a href=&quot;https://heritageposts.tumblr.com/post/623121771590303744/tumblr-university&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/XXCXtwpp7t" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 23:08:00 GMT" tweetId="1420883837337407492" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420883837337407492" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@lochlanoneil, the creator of DashCon, has finally opened up about her time as the architect of one of the internet's most iconic disasters and pivotal moments in internet history &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.garbageday.email/p/meet-lochlan-oneil-the-creator-of&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PMEgcEhzXy" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 21:05:20 GMT" tweetId="1420852967540809730" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420852967540809730" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/broderick/status/1420853355484753930&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 21:07:29 GMT" tweetId="1420853508052426753" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420853508052426753" inReplyToId="1420852967540809730" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="The perfect man doesn't exi— &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/DinahDie/status/1420552300444139520&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 18:39:57 GMT" tweetId="1420816381356904451" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420816381356904451" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Huge get for the Washington Post!! Nathan is one of the best games/streaming/internet culture writers the biz, can't wait to keep reading his work! 🔥🔥🔥 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Vahn16/status/1420813943115862024&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 18:34:49 GMT" tweetId="1420815090715009024" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420815090715009024" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="It's Time To Write &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Kantrowitz/status/1420797699440340998&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 18:12:17 GMT" tweetId="1420809418661265409" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420809418661265409" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@edzitron has become one of the most insightful, prescient writers on work, culture, the internet, and media. Thrilled to see his byline in @TheAtlantic. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2021/07/work-from-home-benefits/619597/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 16:15:13 GMT" tweetId="1420779957102419975" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420779957102419975" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@alexmarvar wrote about the young people grinding on DePop. “Keep doing it, keep listing, keep selling, try your best, and hopefully it will shake out.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/22580446/depop-online-vintage-sales-business-algorithm-dangers&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 15:58:28 GMT" tweetId="1420775742577643523" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420775742577643523" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="They are, and they’re a community we don’t deserve &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ejdickson/status/1420761735556907009&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 15:47:48 GMT" tweetId="1420773058080477189" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420773058080477189" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 28" type="calendarDay" name="28" >
				<outline text="Great and informative piece and glad to see long covid discussed. Yes, vaccines will keep you out of the hospital, but you can still suffer w/ long covid after getting a breakthrough infection. Hope everyone stays safe and gets vaccinated if you aren’t🙏🏻 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/justinjm1/status/1418976010129879050&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 01:41:12 GMT" tweetId="1420560006005420037" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420560006005420037" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The Daily also did a great episode on breakthrough infections that answered all the many questions I (and many others) have probably had lately. Stay safe everyone and get vaccinated! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/26/podcasts/the-daily/coronavirus-vaccines-breakthrough-infections-delta-variant.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 01:43:26 GMT" tweetId="1420560566741999616" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420560566741999616" inReplyToId="1420560006005420037" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I wrote a feature for The Atlantic in 2018 about how influencers were driving hotels crazy and all the horrible and chaotic ways hotels were attempting to work with content creators. Sounds like a great (and overdue!) product! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2018/06/instagram-influencers-are-driving-luxury-hotels-crazy/562679/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/wKViNlz8Wp" type="tweet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2021 00:14:39 GMT" tweetId="1420538224003272705" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420538224003272705" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="What are some of the best products tackling pay disparity in the creator/influencer world?" type="tweet" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 23:52:10 GMT" tweetId="1420532567011258372" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420532567011258372" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
