Madewell: &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1420133434802933762/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 21:26:10 GMT" tweetId="1420133434802933762" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420133434802933762" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“You look up some old internet thing, there was always a furry running it.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.inputmag.com/gaming/how-furries-are-making-virtual-reality-worth-visiting&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 21:07:01 GMT" tweetId="1420128618005499905" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420128618005499905" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I do wish all politicians on all sides would stop using language like this when talking about new technologies. Tech is not some mysterious dark ally area, it's fully integrated into our culture, economy etc. There are ways to critique crypto w/o relying on these kinds of tropes &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1420121568441556994/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 20:39:01 GMT" tweetId="1420121568441556994" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420121568441556994" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="And what about the &quot;shadowy&quot; super- bankers, hollywood execs, powerful incumbents and others who run our legacy systems? Worth noting that they're almost never subject to this same framing" type="tweet" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 20:43:08 GMT" tweetId="1420122603851685892" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1420122603851685892" inReplyToId="1420121568441556994" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
