				<outline text="TikTok Bans Influencers From Promoting Cryptocurrencies &lt;a href=&quot;https://finance.yahoo.com/news/tiktok-bans-influencers-promoting-cryptocurrencies-194500204.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 16:25:02 GMT" tweetId="1416071385001168898" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416071385001168898" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Until someone builds a better alternative, Close Friends might be the closest thing to a good party invite system we’re all gonna get.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/88nd7z/the-only-party-invite-i-want-this-summer-is-via-instagram-close-friends&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/z0F8qsoTXa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 16:14:12 GMT" tweetId="1416068659026477058" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416068659026477058" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I hate the IG close friends invite!!!! It causes so much drama. You don't know who's coming or who saw ur invite, u have to totally re-tailor your CF lists, there's no way for ppl coming to see who ELSE is coming, which makes it awkward. IG just needs an RSVP option in Stories" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 16:16:32 GMT" tweetId="1416069248997367814" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416069248997367814" inReplyToId="1416068659026477058" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="This tweet is very funny but verification as this binary, elusive thing is actually something that needs to be fixed. I wrote about that here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2019/06/instagram-and-twitter-should-eliminate-verification/592351/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/RSz0PqSJ0Y" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 15:51:30 GMT" tweetId="1416062946627751941" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416062946627751941" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="TIL the Social Register has a website &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.socialregisteronline.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:50:04 GMT" tweetId="1416047488268636165" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416047488268636165" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Oh here's a 2018 Robb Report article on how they're trying to modernize saying they actually DO have a few members who are &quot;not white, AngloSaxon, or Protestant.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://129e076a-bbed-ff32-5d4b-c2001cca5b9c.filesusr.com/ugd/ae08e0_753f4fa7c69c40c1ad675f23265399fe.pdf&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:52:59 GMT" tweetId="1416048223093993476" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416048223093993476" inReplyToId="1416047488268636165" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="They started publishing content online too  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.socialregisteronline.com/tale-of-two&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PGAy7J80SJ" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:57:10 GMT" tweetId="1416049275012792323" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416049275012792323" inReplyToId="1416048223093993476" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Of course they published a whole ode to a southern plantation 🥴 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.socialregisteronline.com/a-carolina-plantation-remembered&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:58:53 GMT" tweetId="1416049706082439175" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416049706082439175" inReplyToId="1416049275012792323" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Silicon Valley culture can get bad, but the New England WASP world is really a whole other level of toxic  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.socialregisteronline.com/advertise&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/1n7mPg1Eeg" type="tweet" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 15:02:44 GMT" tweetId="1416050676191408135" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1416050676191408135" inReplyToId="1416049706082439175" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
