			<outline text="July 14" type="calendarDay" name="14" >
				<outline text="Amazing job alert 🚨 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/whoweekly/status/1415320691348492295&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 15 Jul 2021 02:34:33 GMT" tweetId="1415499999283142657" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415499999283142657" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Declaring text bankruptcy &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1415455432487886854/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 23:37:27 GMT" tweetId="1415455432487886854" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415455432487886854" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is really interesting &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/boztank/status/1415416877560565764&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 21:06:38 GMT" tweetId="1415417475639005184" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415417475639005184" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I think the key phrase here is journalistic standards. There's absolutely an opportunity for a more traditional entertainment/news brand to capture that space &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kelsaywhat/status/1415374573416112131&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 18:53:50 GMT" tweetId="1415384056884301825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415384056884301825" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Once again, they should just allow regular tweets to expire! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/verge/status/1415361369348640771&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 17:26:26 GMT" tweetId="1415362062214119425" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415362062214119425" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Twitter says that influencer news page Def Noodles has been permanently suspended  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/def-noodles-twitter-banned-suspended-why-violating-rules-2021-7&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:21:52 GMT" tweetId="1415345814663319561" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415345814663319561" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="EXCLUSIVE: Facebook plans to pay creators $1 billion to use its products. The payouts are part of a broader effort to woo influencers onto its platforms &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/14/technology/facebook-payments-creators.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:20:09 GMT" tweetId="1415345380913524743" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415345380913524743" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The $1 billion will be allocated among creators of all types, giving influencers an incentive for creating and posting original content to Facebook &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/14/technology/facebook-payments-creators.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:22:32 GMT" tweetId="1415345980560580612" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415345980560580612" inReplyToId="1415345380913524743" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Creators can earn money by using specific Facebook and Instagram features or by hitting certain milestones/metrics. If a creator live streams on a regular basis, for instance, they can earn cash. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/14/technology/facebook-payments-creators.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 16:23:08 GMT" tweetId="1415346130687348739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415346130687348739" inReplyToId="1415345980560580612" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Had a blast breaking down the Call Her Daddy $60M deal and what it means for the creator ecosystem w/ the goats @ColinandSamir! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ColinandSamir/status/1415309232602161156&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:47:21 GMT" tweetId="1415337126191898625" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415337126191898625" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="TikTok Becomes the First Non-Facebook Mobile App to Reach 3 Billion Downloads Globally &lt;a href=&quot;https://sensortower.com/blog/tiktok-downloads-3-billion&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 15:22:22 GMT" tweetId="1415330839689408515" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415330839689408515" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I want to meet the person Spotify thinks I am &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1415308061305155584/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 13:51:51 GMT" tweetId="1415308061305155584" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415308061305155584" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is really terrifying, hope everyone stays safe &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/society/2021/jul/13/delta-surge-could-leave-hundreds-of-thousands-with-long-covid&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 14 Jul 2021 10:23:57 GMT" tweetId="1415255741720563712" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415255741720563712" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 13" type="calendarDay" name="13" >
				<outline text="Anyone on here seriously love/miss working from an office and/or thinking about quitting their job if it stays remote only??" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 22:38:27 GMT" tweetId="1415078195259486214" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415078195259486214" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="*please read my tweet, I am not advocating this, I'm just wondering if anyone feels this way! I know there must be some die hard office lovers out there." type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 23:02:47 GMT" tweetId="1415084321921187840" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415084321921187840" inReplyToId="1415078195259486214" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="DefNoodles, a popular drama/tea account that documents influencer news, is currently suspended &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/banishedjourno/status/1415064280664137728&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 22:29:30 GMT" tweetId="1415075943438340099" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415075943438340099" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is an awesome gig I would have jumped at when I was freelance! Check it out &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/markyarm/status/1415010763031339022&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 22:16:24 GMT" tweetId="1415072648418242563" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415072648418242563" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Another absolutely wild story by @IAmAsarch &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/iamasarch/status/1415049836387348481&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 21:01:37 GMT" tweetId="1415053827225554949" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415053827225554949" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@IAmAsarch has an expert ability to break down niche community drama &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/bbw-pearadise-body-postive-tiktok-stefan-wilhelmy-sue-women-defamation-2021-7&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 21:03:03 GMT" tweetId="1415054189017894919" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415054189017894919" inReplyToId="1415053827225554949" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I mean sure &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brobible/status/1415044940128825345&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 21:00:30 GMT" tweetId="1415053547142623237" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415053547142623237" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Companies don't want to pay overtime, then they also don't want to give you extra time off for the amount of work it takes to get a job done. @edzitron on how burnout is not a mental health issue, it is an organizational issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://ez.substack.com/p/the-burnout-conversation-is-a-corporate&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 20:34:16 GMT" tweetId="1415046945081643009" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415046945081643009" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="@edzitron &quot;The cause of burnout is too much work, and the solution to too much work is to make sure people have more time to do their work OR add more people so that they have less work to do.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://ez.substack.com/p/the-burnout-conversation-is-a-corporate&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 20:36:21 GMT" tweetId="1415047469042479109" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1415047469042479109" inReplyToId="1415046945081643009" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="This video plays in my head once a day &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/calebsaysthings/status/1365776466810605569&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2021 16:47:01 GMT" tweetId="1414989755629117446" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414989755629117446" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
