			<outline text="July 12" type="calendarDay" name="12" >
				<outline text="One of the 2010's most pivotal moments in cultural history. We will never be the same &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/broderick/status/1414688305300578308&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 21:04:06 GMT" tweetId="1414692065947136007" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414692065947136007" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bijanstephen/status/1414690876534755340&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 21:22:23 GMT" tweetId="1414696667333414916" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414696667333414916" inReplyToId="1414692065947136007" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I'm at the restaurant. I'm at the stock market. I'm at the combination restaurant and stock market. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/janiraplanes/status/1414688060139360258&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 20:49:57 GMT" tweetId="1414688501833084931" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414688501833084931" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Pretty sure the Science desk has the best headline writers in the newsroom. @michaelroston how can we compete!? 😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/09/science/cuttlefish-cognition-cephalopods.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 20:49:09 GMT" tweetId="1414688304000294912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414688304000294912" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Just me trying to keep up with you!!! 😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kyurieff/status/1414680636095401992&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 20:31:52 GMT" tweetId="1414683953211101186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414683953211101186" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“People’s worst fears about the app come true.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/lmatsakis/status/1414600925453459462&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 18:31:24 GMT" tweetId="1414653637800964096" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414653637800964096" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Had a great time teaming up with @MikeIsaac on this one! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/facebook-creators-tiktok-youtube.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 18:08:40 GMT" tweetId="1414647913347698699" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414647913347698699" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is true! I’ve never been a great writer, but if you’re excellent at uncovering new information and reporting things out, you don’t have to be the most beautiful writer in the room.☺️ &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bonazoulay/status/1414603521467498497&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 15:18:17 GMT" tweetId="1414605036626268161" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414605036626268161" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Isn’t the world much more exciting now that Caroline Calloway could be waiting inside any given bar, waiting to pour Snake Oil on your face?&quot; @kathrynfiona  &lt;a href=&quot;https://embedded.substack.com/p/some-news-our-paid-launch-caroline&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:52:49 GMT" tweetId="1414598627956244484" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414598627956244484" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I just paid to subscribe to @getembedded and you should too! It's an absolutely essential and really thoughtful newsletter on internet culture and the online creator world &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kathrynfiona/status/1414597517778489346&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:51:49 GMT" tweetId="1414598375442419719" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414598375442419719" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="So cool to see this little ~creator economy~ box of my stories on NYT dot com!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/00K0VMxLcc" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:42:08 GMT" tweetId="1414595938556026882" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414595938556026882" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about the consumer investing boom driven by the rise of the &quot;creator economy&quot;, how VCs are embracing the online creator world and what that means for the industry. w/ @erinkwoo  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:31:07 GMT" tweetId="1414593165764579334" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414593165764579334" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Read me and @erinkwoo story on how VCs are going wild for creators! 

“I’ve seen a few posts from V.C.s saying, ‘Eight of the 10 companies I met with today are creator companies. It really is en vogue now.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:33:38 GMT" tweetId="1414593802019409925" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414593802019409925" inReplyToId="1414593165764579334" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="@erinkwoo “There are more creator economy start-ups than creators,” @TurnerNovak, founder of Banana Capital, which invests in early-stage tech start-ups, joked. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:34:08 GMT" tweetId="1414593926883913736" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414593926883913736" inReplyToId="1414593802019409925" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="@erinkwoo @TurnerNovak The word “creator” has become a buzzword in the VC/startup world, appended to all types of businesses to attract investors. So much so that @alexfinden, a tech entrepreneur, coined the term “creator washing.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:35:07 GMT" tweetId="1414594172271607810" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414594172271607810" inReplyToId="1414593926883913736" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="@erinkwoo @TurnerNovak @alexfinden “Older social platforms, those were all about interacting with your friends online,” said @LinusWalton, vice president at the Chernin Group. Now “it’s all about becoming that influencer, or becoming that new TikTok star that all your friends are watching.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:37:19 GMT" tweetId="1414594727484301313" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414594727484301313" inReplyToId="1414594172271607810" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="“For years, no one cared or recognized this space as a space with real money. Now, with money pouring into the industry, we’re only going to see more companies, more competition and more start-ups involving creators as a part of their businesses.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/content-creators-venture-capital.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:38:56 GMT" tweetId="1414595132318486530" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414595132318486530" inReplyToId="1414594727484301313" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I’m back baby &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1414587156165713925/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:07:14 GMT" tweetId="1414587156165713925" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414587156165713925" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="First NYT bathroom selfie in over a year 🥰 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1414606056064442370/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 15:22:20 GMT" tweetId="1414606056064442370" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414606056064442370" inReplyToId="1414587156165713925" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Absolute legends here 👇🏻 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/sheeraf/status/1414585818308567041&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 14:06:16 GMT" tweetId="1414586912300482561" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414586912300482561" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about Facebook’s (very late) efforts to court creators w/ @MikeIsaac &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/12/technology/facebook-creators-tiktok-youtube.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 13:03:30 GMT" tweetId="1414571116144828421" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414571116144828421" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="👇🏻 Just educating creators on their product is going to be important as FB pushes into this space &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kevinbparry/status/1414573406339706881&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 12 Jul 2021 13:14:22 GMT" tweetId="1414573852869505024" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1414573852869505024" inReplyToId="1414571116144828421" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 10" type="calendarDay" name="10" >
				<outline text="“Reality TV but MORE real with MORE content, 24/7” is a good way to describe what the internet has become as creators become more dominate. Another good breakdown by @kattenbarge &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kattenbarge/status/1413929235262197766&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 18:46:28 GMT" tweetId="1413932654098059269" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413932654098059269" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="The quote tweets on this are wild, it’s very common to get a celeb to do red carpet Qs! This takes place often at award shows and other events. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/whoisaddison/status/1413656072678641664&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 12:54:03 GMT" tweetId="1413843965237997569" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413843965237997569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="A celeb asking some easy Qs on the red carpet is not “stealing jobs from those more deserving.” It is their celebrity/fame that qualifies them for that type of opportunity. Having a famous person ask other famous people Qs is a tactic to build buzz and get people to watch" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 12:56:50 GMT" tweetId="1413844665762254851" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413844665762254851" inReplyToId="1413843965237997569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Exactly &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mohamadtm91/status/1413844826760519683&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 12:58:12 GMT" tweetId="1413845009728741376" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413845009728741376" inReplyToId="1413844665762254851" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Yup this too &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mohamadtm91/status/1413845757141024771&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 13:03:51 GMT" tweetId="1413846429911691269" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413846429911691269" inReplyToId="1413845009728741376" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="I think some ppl aren’t aware of how woven into the media ecosystem influencers are. Having over 120M followers across platforms does qualify someone for opportunities like this b/c they’re being hired in a promotional capacity. This is stuff I wish journalism schools would teach &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mtzler/status/1413850796458917891&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2021 13:28:02 GMT" tweetId="1413852516526272512" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413852516526272512" inReplyToId="1413846429911691269" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="This is amazing, what a great team @BostonJoan has assembled! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/JaneLytv/status/1413586949722492928&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 19:55:39 GMT" tweetId="1413587674099855360" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413587674099855360" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Why not both! 😌 @broderick &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1413535590251892739/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 16:28:41 GMT" tweetId="1413535590251892739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413535590251892739" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="What season of Succession is this &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/oliverdarcy/status/1413503572906369033&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 14:37:49 GMT" tweetId="1413507690257473536" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413507690257473536" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Excited for this &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/johncarreyrou/status/1413152952294940679&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:37:46 GMT" tweetId="1413492575365963776" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413492575365963776" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Thank u to everyone who came to hang out with me! Congrats to all of us for making it through this year 💓 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/aaronisnotcool/status/1413324072067518473&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 04:53:35 GMT" tweetId="1413360661741150210" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413360661741150210" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 8" type="calendarDay" name="08" >
				<outline text="😰 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/paulleewr/status/1413234413337563138&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 21:38:49 GMT" tweetId="1413251247562534912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413251247562534912" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="The producers of Queer Eye are on a nationwide search for people with crypto wallets who locked themselves out &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.castingdepot.com/p/cryptocasting&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/xs3wjhGcaJ" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 18:10:46 GMT" tweetId="1413198892812935172" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413198892812935172" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Made it to NYC hacker house TikTok &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/vikushavas/status/1413161535346823179/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 15:54:23 GMT" tweetId="1413164571448287234" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413164571448287234" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Any corporate brand people up for chatting with me about TikTok's new resume feature? Please DM me if so! Would love to hear from companies if they do or don't plan to leverage this &lt;a href=&quot;https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/find-a-job-with-tiktok-resumes&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 14:12:24 GMT" tweetId="1413138907005284363" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413138907005284363" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="How are we supposed to get work done today with links like this floating around!? &lt;a href=&quot;https://slate.com/human-interest/2021/07/cat-person-kristen-roupenian-viral-story-about-me.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 13:38:26 GMT" tweetId="1413130356589350917" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413130356589350917" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is a really shocking story and good reminder of how many of us take clean air for granted &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/charlesornstein/status/1413089716635947008&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 11:28:15 GMT" tweetId="1413097596244144132" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413097596244144132" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="IG meme pages literally devolving into that Matt Bors comic &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1413093822091911170/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 11:13:15 GMT" tweetId="1413093822091911170" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413093822091911170" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Weird! Some of these pages are the ones who ran Bloomberg sponcon too. If anyone else notices big traditional meme pages shifting into politicized content please send to me. Would be interested in looking into &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/shawnragell/status/1413219797366566912&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 19:53:38 GMT" tweetId="1413224777792331781" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413224777792331781" inReplyToId="1413093822091911170" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I'm old enough to remember when this account just reposted months old tweets like &quot;can you marry pizza&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1413538320173391886/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 16:39:32 GMT" tweetId="1413538320173391886" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413538320173391886" inReplyToId="1413224777792331781" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 7" type="calendarDay" name="07" >
				<outline text="I post a lot on here if you think of it as a social media site I guess, but I consider Twitter a chat room" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 03:11:08 GMT" tweetId="1412972491795013632" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412972491795013632" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ice gets it &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/finallevel/status/1202360515298758656&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 03:54:37 GMT" tweetId="1412983434725756933" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412983434725756933" inReplyToId="1412972491795013632" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					<outline text="Lol &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1413172477161844744/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 16:25:48 GMT" tweetId="1413172477161844744" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413172477161844744" inReplyToId="1412972491795013632" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Read @bettinamak on “hot girl food” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/4avqpj/why-is-tinned-fish-hot-girl-food-now&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/3tloIL9GO5" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 03:08:34 GMT" tweetId="1412971847126237186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412971847126237186" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Someone mentioned @edzitron “the substacker” to me today which means he is officially a Newsletter Guy on here" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 02:33:25 GMT" tweetId="1412963001422974980" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412963001422974980" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I love @CreatorsDigest, a 2x a week rundown featuring industry news, company hires, and deep dives on certain influencers. Shout out @shardulgo for putting it together! &lt;a href=&quot;https://creatorsdigest.substack.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:57:07 GMT" tweetId="1412938765207748608" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412938765207748608" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@KaitlynFehr00 on Tana's new “influencer agency.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://berkeleybeacon.com/tana-mongeaus-dizzy-history-of-youtube-controversy/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:54:36 GMT" tweetId="1412938130978705409" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412938130978705409" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@adamlashinsky on the creator boom &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/what-could-go-wrong-with-creator-economy-boom-2021-6&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:48:31 GMT" tweetId="1412936600829497347" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412936600829497347" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Thousands of would-be pop stars mailed demo tapes in a time before streaming, but the record labels didn’t get to sell ads against them. Tech giants benefit massively from the infinite number of hopefuls entering the fray&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wired.com/story/twitch-turns-10-creator-economy/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; by @cecianasta" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:47:14 GMT" tweetId="1412936277343842304" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412936277343842304" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Many of these are great but if I may be so bold as to add a few more....! &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thecut.com/2021/07/newsletter-writers-on-their-favorite-newsletters.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:04:36 GMT" tweetId="1412925550558056450" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412925550558056450" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@Lucas_Shaw's Screentime is essential reading on tech, entertainment, and online creators  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/screentime&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:05:16 GMT" tweetId="1412925715507449857" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412925715507449857" inReplyToId="1412925550558056450" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text=".@arperelli's newsletter on what's new in the business of YouTube, Instagram, and the influencer industry at large. &lt;a href=&quot;https://newsletter.businessinsider.com/join/newsletter.businessinsider.com/join/4np/insider-influencers&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:06:00 GMT" tweetId="1412925901654921222" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412925901654921222" inReplyToId="1412925715507449857" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text=".@kyurieff's newsletter on the business of the online creator world &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theinformation.com/newsletters/creator-economy&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:06:36 GMT" tweetId="1412926050900774912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412926050900774912" inReplyToId="1412925901654921222" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="@kyurieff .@ColinandSamir's creator industry roundup &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thepublishpress.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:07:47 GMT" tweetId="1412926351544307712" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412926351544307712" inReplyToId="1412926050900774912" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="@kyurieff @ColinandSamir And of course @iamaliceophelia and @maidmentfaye's High Tea newsletter on internet culture.   &lt;a href=&quot;https://hightea.substack.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:11:38 GMT" tweetId="1412927321028370432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412927321028370432" inReplyToId="1412926351544307712" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
										<outline text="There are about 100 more I'd add but I'm going to stop here b/c I don't want to seem like some ppl are getting left out. But those are the ones I always click fastest in my inbox!!" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:12:24 GMT" tweetId="1412927512523509761" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412927512523509761" inReplyToId="1412927321028370432" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
											<outline text="Wait also OBVIOUSLY I have to plug my own Substack too. I send it very randomly, whenever I remember. So it will keep you guessing! 😅 It's a great way to keep up with my work! &amp;lt;3 &lt;a href=&quot;https://taylorlorenz.substack.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 00:15:02 GMT" tweetId="1412928172958568451" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412928172958568451" inReplyToId="1412927512523509761" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
											</outline>
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="“It’s time that we see the development of discriminatory technological products as an intentional act done by the largely white male executives of Silicon Valley to uphold the systems of racism, misogyny, ability, class and other axis of oppression…” &lt;a href=&quot;https://slate.com/technology/2021/07/silicon-valley-algorithmic-bias-structural-racism.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 22:25:23 GMT" tweetId="1412900581426049026" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412900581426049026" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Happy one year anniversary of the TikTokcalypse and subsequent Hype House vs Sway Boys showdown &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/tiktokleakins/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/nSoFWUjIs3" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 20:20:41 GMT" tweetId="1412869200096399363" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412869200096399363" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I’ll accept that 😂 is cringe but 🤣 is elite" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 19:01:22 GMT" tweetId="1412849238967455749" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412849238967455749" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="How do I find out about cool crypto events?" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:49:32 GMT" tweetId="1412846260453793792" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412846260453793792" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“Nihilistic lottery” seems like a pretty apt description of our economy right now &lt;a href=&quot;https://luttig.substack.com/p/finance-as-culture&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:52:25 GMT" tweetId="1412816786047782916" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412816786047782916" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="YouTube continues to push misinformation on users, from false election fraud claims to conspiracy theories, to COVID-19 disinfo, and more, according to a new study &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/youtube-algorithm-continues-to-push-misinformation-study-finds-2021-7&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 16:50:32 GMT" tweetId="1412816311588114437" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412816311588114437" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="😭😭😭 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/milesklee/status/1412798773294632961&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 15:44:32 GMT" tweetId="1412799702211469313" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412799702211469313" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Love these trolls let's keep it up &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/BW/status/1412768111292469252&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 14:02:36 GMT" tweetId="1412774052004077569" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412774052004077569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Don't get my hopes up 😭 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/WeAreMel/status/1412765862625484804&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 13:35:42 GMT" tweetId="1412767282657386506" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412767282657386506" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Will all the old editors be back tho? 😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/mel-magazine-dollar-shave-club-recurrent-dc6d1893-3717-419f-a2f6-950458514446.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 14:11:57 GMT" tweetId="1412776403041402886" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412776403041402886" inReplyToId="1412767282657386506" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="😭😭😭 finally something good in this world!!!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/wearemel/status/1412782583369322496&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 15:45:24 GMT" tweetId="1412799921661620230" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412799921661620230" inReplyToId="1412776403041402886" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="In a coma from consuming 4 bagels a day in nyc to make up for lost time" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 13:05:10 GMT" tweetId="1412759596431777793" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412759596431777793" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Terrifying thread, this stuff desperately needs to be taken more seriously &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/goddammitsarah/status/1412434922636120065&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 05:07:59 GMT" tweetId="1412639510417055745" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412639510417055745" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/reductress/status/1412501693653258242&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 03:32:44 GMT" tweetId="1412615541865525253" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412615541865525253" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Roblox strippers breaking down monetization &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rugbrat69/status/1412562375216185347&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/AK51WdsXsd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 01:46:33 GMT" tweetId="1412588819476516865" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412588819476516865" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is an interesting idea. Personally I really love and miss the office, but I also spent a lot of my office time socializing with coworkers and bothering @Jonesieman 😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/edzitron/status/1412531957569757186&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 22:14:42 GMT" tweetId="1412535502914396170" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412535502914396170" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Summer 2021 mood &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/EmojiMashupBot/status/1409934745895583750&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 20:46:00 GMT" tweetId="1412513180966809603" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412513180966809603" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This is such a fantastic, essential piece. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/VICENews/status/1412435959694741508&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 19:30:33 GMT" tweetId="1412494194913038339" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412494194913038339" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I keep being introduced as being a Forbes 30 under 30 😅. No hate, but I've never been on any 30 under 30 list (I spent the majority of my 20s working temp jobs).Ty to everyone for assuming I'm much younger/more successful than I am!! I do not support any age based lists though&amp;lt;3" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:48:38 GMT" tweetId="1412453447530594310" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412453447530594310" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="No, I'm 50 and thriving &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/DanGarcia1980/status/1412453679240826885&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:51:09 GMT" tweetId="1412454080723800068" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412454080723800068" inReplyToId="1412453447530594310" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="“I’m scared that no matter what I do, I’ve become an enemy of the mob. No matter what I do, I’m just going to get hate” Good piece on what happened to @deannaschwartzz &amp;amp; what young journalists (especially women/POC) have to deal w/ in today's media climate &lt;a href=&quot;https://studyhall.xyz/newsletters/digest-07-06-2021/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:33:20 GMT" tweetId="1412449596668788739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412449596668788739" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Everyone who uses social media inherently portrays a certain version of themselves while omitting the rest; playacting is the essence of the internet...Still, it’s become easier than ever to assume an almost entirely new identity online&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-goods/2021/7/6/22561197/coconutkitty-diana-deets-itsnotdatsrs-asianfishing-deepfake-catfish&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:35:32 GMT" tweetId="1412435052366008325" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412435052366008325" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="🔥🔥🔥 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/erinkwoo/status/1412431730326130691&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:26:38 GMT" tweetId="1412432811164844032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412432811164844032" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Asher is not part of a typical influencer collective. He is one of many members of a 29-person 'system,'  all of whom share a single body, brain, and life.&quot; Fascinating longread on Dissociative Identity Disorder TikTok by @stealthywriter_ in @inputmag &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.inputmag.com/culture/dissociative-identity-disorder-did-tiktok-influencers-multiple-personalities&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:23:04 GMT" tweetId="1412431912430342145" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412431912430342145" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="There are so many products that have gone viral on TikTok that people are opening stores dedicated to them. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-goods/22555723/tiktok-viral-products-cerave-sky-high-mascara-amazon-leggings&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:10:19 GMT" tweetId="1412428705616572417" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412428705616572417" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Iconic collab between 2 of my fave social media/creator economy experts @brendangahan @JayHoovy &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brendangahan/status/1412424947889278976&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:56:42 GMT" tweetId="1412425278060646412" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412425278060646412" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This looks awesome for anyone in NYC on Aug 17th &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.caveat.nyc/event/digital-void-the-meme-in-the-moment-festival-8-17-2021&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:49:13 GMT" tweetId="1412423392628727825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412423392628727825" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I'm not but it looks like an unbeatable lineup! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Samcornwell/status/1412423848293769223&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:51:24 GMT" tweetId="1412423944414679047" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412423944414679047" inReplyToId="1412423392628727825" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Ahh the greatest station in nyc &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412392553329172485/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:46:40 GMT" tweetId="1412392553329172485" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412392553329172485" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@carolinecaloway is launching a skincare line called “snake oil” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412383512750084097/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:10:44 GMT" tweetId="1412383512750084097" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412383512750084097" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ingredients TK &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412385585516396549/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:18:59 GMT" tweetId="1412385585516396549" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412385585516396549" inReplyToId="1412383512750084097" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="It’s worth noting that (as with all creator products), many fans will not care if this works or not, they are buying into the lifestyle and just want to support their fave. Because she’s not a beauty or skincare influencer people don’t expect much so she has not authority to lose" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:22:20 GMT" tweetId="1412386428806479873" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412386428806479873" inReplyToId="1412385585516396549" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						<outline text="It’s worth noting that (as with all creator products), many fans will not care if this works or not, they are buying into the lifestyle and just want to support their fave. Because she’s not a beauty or skincare influencer people don’t expect much so she has no authority to lose" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:23:01 GMT" tweetId="1412386604216459267" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412386604216459267" inReplyToId="1412385585516396549" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Exactly! It will generate deep backlash from the skincare/beauty community and ppl online (has already started), which ultimately generates more attention, which can then be monetized and leads to more success online. 😌 Certain creators are masters of this cycle &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/saharaarshad/status/1412386627394043908&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:25:55 GMT" tweetId="1412387333765165057" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412387333765165057" inReplyToId="1412386604216459267" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Petition for someone from @InternetInsider to do a full review slideshow b/c I need to know 😅 @linzasaur" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:12:08 GMT" tweetId="1412414060939956230" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412414060939956230" inReplyToId="1412387333765165057" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="These fake livestreams are becoming way too common. Seen several of influencers like Charli, Addison etc as well. They usually choose really personal Lives (a popular one is one where Charli is crying), also the watermelon rubber band guy. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nickabouzeid/status/1412267091177136131&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 11:19:16 GMT" tweetId="1412370557887209472" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412370557887209472" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="This movement would not last one day on the streets of nyc &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mkarolian/status/1412242867913957379&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 03:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1412245891956752384" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412245891956752384" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Feature or a bug? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ztpetrizzo/status/1412077526986465284&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 02:13:19 GMT" tweetId="1412233164098056193" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412233164098056193" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“Ivermectin, the authors added, ‘is not a viable option to treat COVID-19.” Yet proponents of the drug’s “holy war has taken on new vigor as prominent members of the ‘Intellectual Dark Web’ have begun advocating for the drug” Good breakdown by @annamerlan &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/y3d5gv/ivermectin-covid-treatment-advocates-rogan-weinstein-hecker&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:51:31 GMT" tweetId="1412197482050867200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412197482050867200" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ivermectin, as @annamerlan reports, has become a flashpoint to many in the anti-media crowd &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/y3d5gv/ivermectin-covid-treatment-advocates-rogan-weinstein-hecker&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PUi1EOyOf5" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:54:06 GMT" tweetId="1412198130045554688" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412198130045554688" inReplyToId="1412197482050867200" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Artists have begun sharing their work under the hashtag #FixTheAlgorithm to critique the perceived lack of distribution art gets in the feed. h/t @willgonyer &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bugdotpng/status/1412075956890648586&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:45:04 GMT" tweetId="1412195856606957572" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412195856606957572" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="TikTok star Swavy aka Babyfaces has died at age of 18. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@babyface.s?_d=secCgYIASAHKAESMgowwwr4kNzYNEtJcWXfGbdlJvYExepUv3hEjXiuQ5937TgUXIc7lU8QsAuxRAyHY9L2GgA%3D&amp;checksum=01c55bddbac80b0d4181bc3be1a02c6d82b91afff3223097b495984d23ba762d&amp;language=en&amp;sec_uid=MS4wLjABAAAAqXmC8UrKiGYi3jWkfvcU5Ahp1twri7ZqkUhSJ1ebcH1ymyZiNdZe0bu5c5kWdsCI&amp;sec_user_id=MS4wLjABAAAA4BgIbw0ed4-DdJrkIGl8b-Z7qVcLSeJC8LSb_o3Q8_UKKEk1hoyPyATFAQmpe-Go&amp;share_app_id=1233&amp;share_author_id=6798237097989030918&amp;share_link_id=21ABDA18-F232-44B9-8E0D-93219792C726&amp;tt_from=copy&amp;u_code=6dc3cefl1fi8a&amp;user_id=144377784793104384&amp;utm_campaign=client_share&amp;utm_medium=ios&amp;utm_source=copy&amp;source=h5_m&amp;_r=1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/MNaoyz1Gn1" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 22:12:25 GMT" tweetId="1412172541284790273" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412172541284790273" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Local news is reporting that Swavy aka Matima Miller was identified as the victim of a Monday morning homicide &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.delawareonline.com/story/news/crime/2021/07/06/swavy-death-dancing-tiktok-star-babyface-s-shooting-victim-wilmington-delaware/7872252002/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 17:03:10 GMT" tweetId="1412457103252508673" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412457103252508673" inReplyToId="1412172541284790273" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="As usual, creators have begun ripping Swavy's final posts to IG Stories and the IG Stories of his friends/family to repackage his &quot;last moments&quot; as content for YouTube &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412457734931365888/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 17:05:40 GMT" tweetId="1412457734931365888" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412457734931365888" inReplyToId="1412457103252508673" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="This unfortunately says everything about Wendy and who and what TV media pays attention to and nothing about Swavy, who was very much a star in his own right. Really hard to watch &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rach_greenspan/status/1413560217887989769&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 20:07:33 GMT" tweetId="1413590667385782274" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1413590667385782274" inReplyToId="1412457734931365888" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
